TITLE: Configuring Kafka Exporter and Prometheus Scrape in Alloy
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to set up a Kafka exporter, configure Prometheus scraping, and send metrics to a remote write endpoint. It includes setting up the Kafka exporter, defining a scrape job, and configuring remote write with authentication.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/alloy/blob/main/docs/sources/reference/components/prometheus/prometheus.exporter.kafka.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: alloy
CODE:
```
prometheus.exporter.kafka "example" {
  kafka_uris = ["localhost:9200"]
}

// Configure a prometheus.scrape component to send metrics to.
prometheus.scrape "demo" {
  targets    = prometheus.exporter.kafka.example.targets
  forward_to = [prometheus.remote_write.demo.receiver]
}

prometheus.remote_write "demo" {
  endpoint {
    url = "<PROMETHEUS_REMOTE_WRITE_URL>"

    basic_auth {
      username = "<USERNAME>"
      password = "<PASSWORD>"
    }
  }
}
```

