TITLE: Creating Debug Files for Symbol Resolution in Bash
DESCRIPTION: Commands to create separate debug files for stripped binaries to ensure symbols can be resolved properly. This process creates a debug file, strips the original binary, and links them together.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grafana/alloy/blob/main/docs/sources/reference/components/pyroscope/pyroscope.ebpf.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
